Till date there was only Kailasa doing some work in bringing real Folk out to the people. Usually anything in vernacular gets stamped as Folk which is not the case. Tip Top was outstanding. KK proved why he is probably the best male singer in the movies.

snippet.textDisplay: CS India's first episode was an okay start but frankly the show will take time to hit its stride. It was not until season 2 that I feel CS Pakistan really found its groove. 1st thing 1st this show "Coke Studio" is not found in Pakistan.

The programme originated in Brazil as "Coco Cola Studio”, the programme is owned by Coca Cola. 

So There is no way India is trying to copy or imitate the show of Pakistan's Coke Studio Version.

In Pakistani Coke Studio you saw it was like Urdu, Punjabi or some time Persian, Afghani Folk.

Now in Indian Coke Studio  You will see a combination of language as you know Indian has around 346 languages & with classical & Folk Music.
